        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 27 at 9:48AM EDT by NWS Morristown TN</headline>
        <description>At 947 AM EDT, the radar indicated a strong thunderstorm over
Sevierville. A member of the public reported pea sized hail in
downtown Sevierville at 938 AM. This thunderstorm was nearly
stationary.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Public.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Sevierville, Pigeon Forge, McMahan, and Harrisburg.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
